  "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds `DIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_IMAGES` — a per-repository (image-name) allowlist for dind-box host-image passthrough (issue #97). It scopes passthrough to **specific repositories / image names**, one level finer than the registry allowlist (`DIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_REGISTRIES`), so a deployment can seed the inner daemon with **only** the images it owns rather than every public image on the host.\n\nFixes #97.\n\n### Behavior\n\n- **Empty / unset (default)** → unchanged: mode (`off`/`public`/`all`) + registry filter only.\n- **Non-empty** → a host image must match the mode filter **and** at least one space-separated pattern (shell glob). It only ever *narrows* the eligible set — `public` still requires a public `RepoDigest`, so the security guarantee is preserved even if a local/private image matches a pattern.\n- Patterns match against several normalized forms of each reference, so `konard/hive-mind` matches `konard/hive-mind:latest` and the registry-qualified `docker.io/konard/hive-mind:latest` alike. Globs and explicit tags work too.\n\n```sh\n# seed only hive-mind's own images into the nested daemon\nDIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH=public\nDIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_IMAGES=\"konard/hive-mind konard/hive-mind-dind\"\n# globs / tags / registry-qualified refs also work:\nDIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_IMAGES=\"docker.io/konard/hive-mind* konard/hive-mind-dind:latest\"\n```\n\n### Changes\n\n- `ubuntu/24.04/dind/dind-entrypoint.sh` — new `DIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_IMAGES` var + `host_image_matches_images_filter()`, composed into `host_image_passes_filter()`; the passthrough log line now reports the active allowlist.\n- `experiments/preload-unit-test.sh` — 5 new cases (14–18): allowlist scoping, composition with the mode gate, globs / docker.io-qualified / tagged patterns, empty-list back-compat, and direct helper-normalization checks. **41/41 pass locally.**\n- `tests/dind/example-preload-images.sh` — new integration case: `all` mode + an allowlist scoped to one repo copies only that repo and skips the public host image, proving the *allowlist* (not the mode) is what narrows the set.\n- `docs/dind/USAGE.md`, `README.md` — documented the new knob (env table row + \"Scoping to specific images\" section).\n- `.changeset/dind-host-passthrough-images.md` — `bump: minor`.\n\n### How to verify\n\n```bash\nbash experiments/preload-unit-test.sh           # 41 passed, 0 failed\nDIND_IMAGE=box-dind-js tests/dind/example-preload-images.sh   # full CI integration\n```\n\n---\n*Filed from `link-assistant/hive-mind#1879`.*\n",
